Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
calculate_noise_margin(25.10)                    calculate_noise_margin(25.10)

Name
       calculate_noise_margin  -  Specifies  to  calculate  noise margins with
       worst voltages on the driver-receiver pins

Syntax
       calculate_noise_margin

       [-help]

       -noise_limit_file <input_file>

       -power_directory <dir>

       -state_directory <dir>

       Specifies to calculate noise margins with worst voltages on the driver-
       receiver pins. To run this command, you need to specify the default  or
       cell-specific noise limit, signal noise, guardband, rail directory, and
       power directory. Before running the calculate_noise_margin command, you
       need  to specify the set_power_analysis_mode -create_driver_db true pa-
       rameter to generate the driver-receiver database.

       The use model of the command is:

       set_power_analysis_mode ... -create_driver_db true

       calculate_noise_margin -noise_limit_file <input_file>  -state_directory
       <dir> -power_directory <file>

       The  command generates the noise margin output file in the state direc-
       tory. The format of the noise margin output file (<powernetname_ground-
       netname>.noise_margin) is:

       NMH - signal noise - guardband
              NMI - signal noise - guardband

              Voh - Vih

              Vil - Vol

              VDD_driver - VSS_receiver

              VSS_driver - VSS_receiver

              (1-noise_limit)*(VDD_receiver - VSS_receiver)

              noise_limit is the noise limit  value  specified  in  the  noise
              limit file

              noise_limit*(VDD_receiver - VSS_receiver)

              noise_limit  is  the  noise  limit  value specified in the noise
              limit file Signal noise value specified in the noise limit file

              Guardband value specified in the noise limit file

              Driver pin name

              Receiver pin name

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each calculate_noise_margin parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man calculate_noise_margin

       -noise_limit_file <input_file>
              Specifies  the  name of the input noise limit file that contains
              the default or cell-specific  noise  limit,  signal  noise,  and
              guardband. The format of the noise limit file is:

              default_noise_limit <<value>>

              default_signal_noise <<value>>

              default_guard_band <<value>>

              <<cell_name>> <<noise_limit>> <<signal_noise>> <<guard_band>>

              The following is a snippet of the noise limit file:

              default_noise_limit 0.46

              default_signal_noise 0.1

              default_guard_band 0.05

       -power_directory <dir>
              Specifies  the  path to the power directory to access driver-re-
              ceiver pairs.

       -state_directory <dir>
              Specifies the path to the  state  directory  generated  by  rail
              analysis to access EIV database.

Examples
              * The following command calculates noise margin:

                calculate_noise_margin      -noise_limit_file     ./noiselimit
                -state_directory  dynamic_rail/core_105C_dynamic_1  -power_di-
                rectory dynamic_power

